g.text: Read a tab separated csv file
First performs the quality control with FastQC, followed by trimming and clipping with the RawReadManipulator and quality control again with FastQC
afterwards. Filtered read data is mapped to the reference genome with BWA and quantified with FeatureCounts. The FeatureCountsMerger combines
separate read count files into one table to use for differential gene expression analysis.
First filter out genes with very low read counts. Then perform
differential gene expression with the DESeq node. The CSV
Reader should read the annotation matrix in tabular format. The
CSV writer writes the deseq results to a csv file.
